com.github.dylon.liblevenshtein.levenshtein

Class State

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.dylon.liblevenshtein.levenshtein.State
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IState

    public class State
extends Object
implements IState
    Levenshtein state that is used by all algorithms. The algorithm-specific components are injected via setters, so State doesn't need to be coupled to specific implementations.
    Since:
    2.1.0

      • getOuter

        public int[] getOuter(int index)
        One of two cursors maintained in this state, which returns the position at the requested index. Subsequent requests for positions at the immediately proceeding or preceding indices will begin at the index of the last position requested, so lookup for consecutive positions is fast.

        IState.getOuter(int) is used within the outer loops of UnsubsumeFunctions.

        Specified by:
        getOuter in interface IState
        Parameters:
        index - Location of the position to return
        Returns:
        Position vector at the requested index.
        See Also:
        IState.getInner(int)

      • getInner

        public int[] getInner(int index)
        One of two cursors maintained in this state, which returns the position at the requested index. Subsequent requests for positions at the immediately proceeding or preceding indices will begin at the index of the last position requested, so lookup for consecutive positions is fast.

        IState.getInner(int) is used within the inner loops of UnsubsumeFunctions.

        Specified by:
